==English==

===Etymology===
based on the fact that the strategy would not work on a moonlit night, such that the would-be pirate cussed the moon

===Noun===
'''mooncusser'''
# A land-based [[pirate]] who, on dark nights along dangerous [[coast]]s, would demolish any legitimate [[lighthouse]]s or [[beacon]]s, erect a decoy [[signal fire]] in a different, deliberately misleading location, and then, after having induced a [[shipwreck]], subdue any survivors and plunder the wreckage for valuables.

===Synonyms===
* [[wrecker]]

